# Rule: Intelligent Routing

Before responding to ANY development request, perform a silent analysis:

## 1. Classify the request

| Type | Examples |
|---|---|
| QUESTION | "How does X work?", "What is Y?" |
| QUICK_FIX | 1 file, zero ambiguity, known pattern |
| FEATURE | New functionality, multiple files |
| BUG | Error, failure, unexpected behavior |
| REVIEW | Review code, audit, check quality |
| DESIGN | UI, UX, layout, visual component |
| UNCLEAR | Vague request — ask for clarification first |

For QUESTION and UNCLEAR: respond directly without routing. For the rest: continue.

## 2. Detect domains

Analyze the request's keywords and context:

| Keyword/Context | Domain |
|---|---|
| component, page, layout, UI, screen, modal, form, dashboard, tailwind, shadcn | FRONTEND |
| API, route, Server Action, database, schema, query, Prisma, endpoint | BACKEND |
| auth, JWT, RLS, permission, password, token, CSRF, SQL injection, pentest | SECURITY |
| test, spec, playwright, coverage, mock, TDD, E2E | TESTING |
| deploy, CI, GitHub Actions, Vercel, env, pipeline, Docker, infra | DEVOPS |
| performance, slow, optimization, bundle, cache, N+1, Lighthouse, profiling | PERFORMANCE |
| bug, error, exception, stack trace, crash, 500, debug | DEBUG |
| refactor, clean up, organize, simplify, legacy | REFACTOR |
| mobile, React Native, Flutter, iOS, Android, touch, mobile app | MOBILE |
| game, sprite, game loop, Unity, Godot, multiplayer, 2D, 3D | GAME |
| database, schema design, indexing, migration, ORM | DATABASE |
| SEO, ranking, meta tags, sitemap, E-E-A-T, search engine | SEO |
| documentation, docs, README, manual, changelog, ADR | DOCS |
| REST, GraphQL, tRPC, API design, rate limit, versioning | API_DESIGN |
| new project, scaffolding, template, boilerplate, create app | SCAFFOLDING |
| Rust, cargo, ownership, borrowing | RUST |
| Python, FastAPI, Django, Flask, pip | PYTHON |
| bash, shell, Linux, terminal, PowerShell, Windows | INFRA |
| brainstorm, idea, explore a problem, ideation | IDEATION |
| GEO, AI search, LLM visibility, Perplexity, ChatGPT ranking | GEO |
| visualize plan, visual breakdown, interactive HTML, present spec, agency delivery | VISUALIZATION |
| premium, awwwards, agency, $150k, magnetic, GSAP, perpetual motion, bento 2.0, double-bezel, liquid glass, scrolltelling | DESIGN_TASTE |
| minimalist editorial, Notion style, Linear style, warm monochrome, Apple-tier, soft premium, brutalist, industrial, Swiss, CRT terminal, blueprint UI | DESIGN_MODE |
| redesign, modernize UI, visual upgrade, remove AI look, site looks like a template, improve current design | REDESIGN |
| Google Stitch, DESIGN.md (export), Stitch prompt, semantic design system | STITCH_EXPORT |
| complete output, no placeholder, no `// ...`, no `// TODO`, exhaustive, don't cut off | OUTPUT_QUALITY |
| automatic mode, yolo, headless, CI mode, auto-approve, no confirmation, autonomous | AUTO_MODE |
| compress context, compact, summary, near the limit, context full, /compact | CONTEXT_FULL |
| review my skill, validate my rule, lint config, hook conflict, is my skill good? | CONFIG_REVIEW |
| stuck, loop, not progressing, forgets what it was doing, recover session | STUCK |

